ndex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615389\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615389\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 20, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qff1665702581606.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qff1665702581606.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qff1665702581606.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qff1665702581606\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Defines the position and size of a rectangle to use as an anchor for a popup form, in character cells or pixels. The default value is <code class=\"ph codeph\">0,0,0,0</code>.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106421e1_d106422e1_d106423e1\">PopupRect<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">xpos</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">ypos</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">xsize</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">ysize</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"qff1665702581606__table_d12563e1_d12564e1_d12565e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qff1665702581606__table_d12563e1_d12564e1_d12565e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qff1665702581606__table_d12563e1_d12564e1_d12565e1__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qff1665702581606__table_d12563e1_d12564e1_d12565e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">xpos</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">ypos</var><p class=\"p\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">xpos</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">ypos</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qff1665702581606__table_d12563e1_d12564e1_d12565e1__entry__2\">Starting position of the popup window, expressed\n                     as <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>, positive, or negative numbers relative to the top left\n                     corner of the widget; in character cells by default, or in pixels if\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code> is specified.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qff1665702581606__table_d12563e1_d12564e1_d12565e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">xsize</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">ysize</var>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">xsize</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">ysize</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code></p></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qff1665702581606__table_d12563e1_d12564e1_d12565e1__entry__2\">Dimensions of the popup rectangle; in character\n                     cells by default, or in pixels if <code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code> is specified.<p class=\"p\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">xsize</var> and <var class=\"keyword varname\">ysize</var> can be\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> or larger, but not negative.</p></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qff1665702581606__section_qs4_k53_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d991208e196\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"qff1665702581606__table_d11987e1_d11988e1_d11989e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Dynamic?</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Yes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Supported in Grid?</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Dependencies:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qff1665702581606__section_inb_453_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d991208e242\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106430e1_d106431e1_d106432e1\">The PopupRect property provides precise control for\n            positioning a popup form. It can only be set in ProcScript, using\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106433e1_d106434e1_d106435e1\">By default, a popup form is anchored to the bottom\n            left corner of a field and drops down to the right. The anchor corner and direction can\n            be changed with the form's Position property, but the popup window always appears\n            outside the widget boundaries. This not always fine-grained enough. You may want to\n            overlay the contents of a field, or display a popup inside a large field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106436e1_d106437e1_d106438e1\">When PopupRect is defined, it is used as an anchor\n            for the popup form, instead of the widget boundaries. The top left corner of the\n            rectangle can be inside or outside the widget.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106439e1_d106440e1_d106441e1\">If the defined position is outside the screen\n            border, the popup form will be centered in the middle of the screen. This can occur if\n            the PopupRect is too large to fit on the screen, or if it is positioned on or outside\n            the screen border. This ensures that if the application runs on a smaller screen than it\n            is designed for, the popup form will always be visible.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106442e1_d106443e1_d106444e1\">The PopupRect property affects all popup forms\n            anchored to a field. You can first instantiate a popup form without the PopupRect\n            property and then set the property to instantiate another popup. If both popup instances\n            remain open, the anchor point of the first popup changes when the size or position of\n            the anchor field changes. This triggers Uniface to reevaluate the position of all popup\n            instances and use the current value of the PopupRect property for all instances, even\n            when the different popups were instantiated with a different value.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qff1665702581606__section_dq1_553_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d991208e267\">Example: Setting in ProcScript </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106448e1_d106449e1_d106450e1\">The following ProcScript sets the PopupRect\n            property for field WID, and displays a form in a drop-down window.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"qff1665702581606__pre_tpn_v53_zwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;Detail trigger of WID field\nnewinstance \"POPUPFRM\", \"Popup\", \"windowtype=popup\"\n$fieldproperties(FLD1) = \"popuprect=5,1,100px,10px\"\nactivate \"Popup\"\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"qff1665702581606__fig_d106451e1_d106452e1_d106453e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Popup Window for Popup Rectangle in Field</figcaption>\n<br/><img alt=\"Popup rectangle in field example\" class=\"image\" id=\"qff1665702581606__image_zn5_3v3_zwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/popuprecta.png?_LANG=enus\"/><br/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qff1665702581606__section_gmk_kv3_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d991208e292\">Applies To</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qff1665702581606__p_d106460e1_d106461e1_d106462e1\">All widgets except the Grid widget.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"qff1665702581606__ul_uyq_lv3_zwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42098e1_d42099e1_d42100e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fxi1688449052174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxi1688449052174.html\" title=\"The ucheckbox widget enables the user to set a Boolean value in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called CheckBox, which is mapped to ucheckbox.\">ucheckbox (CheckBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42101e1_d42102e1_d42103e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zfr1695290811319.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zfr1695290811319.html\" title=\"Start the Microsoft Windows Color dialog box.\">colorbox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42104e1_d42105e1_d42106e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gzs1665702629046.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gzs1665702629046.html\" title=\"The (ucolorlist) widget displays a list of system or web colors for selection in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called ColorList, which is mapped to ucolorlist.\">ucolorlist (ColorList)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42107e1_d42108e1_d42109e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vmo1688449724415.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmo1688449724415.html\" title=\"The ucombobox widget combines an input field with a drop-down list. It allows users to select one item from a previously defined list, or enter their own data instead. It is applicable only to form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called ComboBox, which is mapped to ucombobox.\">ucombobox (Combo Box)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42110e1_d42111e1_d42112e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrc1665702631553.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrc1665702631553.html\" title=\"The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by clicking the button.\">CommandButton</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42113e1_d42114e1_d42115e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wrn1665702633674.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wrn1665702633674.html\" title=\"The DropTarget logical widget accepts input dragged from a DragSource, other Uniface application, or Microsoft Windows Explorer. The data that is transferred consists of a Uniface list.\">DropTarget</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42116e1_d42117e1_d42118e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fud1688450548955.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fud1688450548955.html\" title=\"The udropdownlist widget is a field-level widget that can display a list of valid options in a list below the input field, so that the user can select one. It is applicable only to form components.\">udropdownlist (DropDownList)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42119e1_d42120e1_d42121e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gev1665702640020.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gev1665702640020.html\" title=\"The ucontainer widget embeds a non-modal form in a field of the current form. Uniface provides a logical widget called FormContainer, which is mapped to ucontainer.\">ucontainer (FormContainer)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42122e1_d42123e1_d42124e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"klb1688454363706.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/klb1688454363706.html\" title=\"Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\">EditBox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42125e1_d42126e1_d42127e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dzy1665702618507.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dzy1665702618507.html\" title=\"This property determines whether the widget behaves as a hyperlink (True; default) or a dynamic label False.\">Hyperlink</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42128e1_d42129e1_d42130e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ied1665702642247.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ied1665702642247.html\" title=\"The uhtml widget is a field-level widget in a form component that renders HTML code (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) or displays a web page (when the field value is a URL prefixed by an ampersand (&amp;www.mysite.com/doc/index.html). Uniface provides a logical widget called HTML, which is mapped to uhtml.\">uhtml (HTML Widget)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42131e1_d42132e1_d42133e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rez1688451198680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rez1688451198680.html\" title=\"The ulistbox widget is a field-level widget that displays an open list in which one or more values can be selected. It can only be used in form components.\">ulistbox (ListBox )</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42134e1_d42135e1_d42136e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gls1665702643795.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gls1665702643795.html\" title=\"The umap widget defines areas on an image that allow the user to interact by clicking on that area. It can only be used in form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called Map, which is mapped to umap.\">umap (Map)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42137e1_d42138e1_d42139e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bwv1665702644903.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bwv1665702644903.html\" title=\"The umeter widget displays the value of a Numeric field on a gauge for which there is a predefined range of values marked around the outer edge. Uniface provides a logical widget called Meter, which is mapped to umeter.\">umeter (Meter)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42140e1_d42141e1_d42142e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"svk1665702646925.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svk1665702646925.html\" title=\"The umonthcalendar widget displays a month calendar to enable the user to select a date. Uniface provides a logical widget called MonthCalendar, which is mapped to umonthcalendar.\">(umonthcalendar) MonthCalendar</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42143e1_d42144e1_d42145e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vvo1665702647716.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vvo1665702647716.html\" title=\"The uOcxContainer widget embeds a Microsoft OCX control into a form component, and maps OCX properties and OCX events to fields and triggers. You can use ProcScript to activate OCX methods and let the OCX control activate widget triggers to respond to OCX events.\">uOcxContainer (OcxContainer)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42146e1_d42147e1_d42148e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rdo1665702649920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rdo1665702649920.html\" title=\"The uOleContainer widget displays an embedded OLE object, enabling you to define links to OLE objects in Uniface applications.\">uOleContainer (OleContainer)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42149e1_d42150e1_d42151e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ddd1665702643397.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ddd1665702643397.html\" title=\"The uoutputbox widget displays streaming text data. The data may come from a specified Output Channel, or be explicitly added. By default, it does not listen to any channel. Uniface provides a logical widget called OutputBox, which is mapped to uoutputbox.\">uoutputbox (OutputBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42152e1_d42153e1_d42154e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rgn1665702634165.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgn1665702634165.html\" title=\"Image to use as the background image on the map widget.\">Image Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42155e1_d42156e1_d42157e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1665702650577.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1665702650577.html\" title=\"The uradiogroup widget displays a set of mutually exclusive choices as a group of radio buttons. Uniface provides a logical widget called RadioGroup, which is mapped to uradiogroup.\">uradiogroup (RadioGroup)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42158e1_d42159e1_d42160e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwk1688451210612.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwk1688451210612.html\" title=\"The urtfeditbox widget is used to display and edit text as Rich Text Format (RTF), which supports formatting such as font and color attributes, text alignment, indentation, and lists. Uniface provides a logical widget called RichEditBox, which is mapped to urtfeditbox.\">urtfeditbox (RichEditBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42161e1_d42162e1_d42163e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"foe1665702651174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/foe1665702651174.html\" title=\"The uslider widget allows users to edit a numeric value in a field by sliding an indicator in a set of a previously defined range of values. Uniface provides a logical widget called Slider, which is mapped to uslider.\">uslider (Slider)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42164e1_d42165e1_d42166e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lxs1665702651483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lxs1665702651483.html\" title=\"The uspinbutton widget enables the user to enter or select a numeric value by clicking a button to increase or decrease a value by a predefined interval within a predefined range. Uniface provides a logical widget called SpinButton, which is mapped to uspinbutton.\">uspinbutton (SpinButton)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42167e1_d42168e1_d42169e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bzj1665702641924.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzj1665702641924.html\" title=\"The utab widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tab, which is mapped to utab.\">utab (Tab)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42170e1_d42171e1_d42172e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gyf1688451219719.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gyf1688451219719.html\" title=\"The utabex widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. The utabex widget is highly customizable, allowing extensive control over the appearance and behavior of the tabs. Uniface provides a logical widget called TabEx, which is mapped to utabex.\">utabex (TabEx)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qff1665702581606__li_d42173e1_d42174e1_d42175e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gge1665702634237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gge1665702634237.html\" title=\"The utree widget enables users to view and navigate structured data as a hierarchy. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tree, which is mapped to utree.\">utree (Tree)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rhe1665702581016.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Popup Window</a><p>A popup window displays a form in a secondary window that is anchored to a field. The position of the popup window is configurable, so that it can be displayed outside or inside the boundaries of its parent field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jcx1665702581523.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Position</a><p>Form instance property that defines the position of a popup form relative to its anchor object, which can be a field, popup rectangle, or mouse cursor. The value specifies an edge or corner from which the window starts, and the direction in which it is displayed. This property can be set in ProcScript using newinstance and $windowproperties.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615389\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615389\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Popup Rectangle (PopupRect) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 20, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Defines the position and size of a rectangle to use as an anchor for a popup form, in character cells or pixels. The default value is 0,0,0,0 . PopupRect = \" xpos { px } , ypos { px } , xsize { px } , ysize { px } \" Table 1. Values Value Meaning xpos , ypos xpos px , ypos px Starting position of the popup window, expressed as 0 , positive, or negative numbers relative to the top left corner of the widget; in character cells by default, or in pixels if px is specified. xsize , ysize xsize px , ysize px Dimensions of the popup rectangle; in character cells by default, or in pixels if px is specified. xsize and ysize can be 0 or larger, but not negative. Usage Dynamic? Yes Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: None Description The PopupRect property provides precise control for positioning a popup form. It can only be set in ProcScript, using $fieldproperties . By default, a popup form is anchored to the bottom left corner of a field and drops down to the right. The anchor corner and direction can be changed with the form's Position property, but the popup window always appears outside the widget boundaries. This not always fine-grained enough. You may want to overlay the contents of a field, or display a popup inside a large field. When PopupRect is defined, it is used as an anchor for the popup form, instead of the widget boundaries. The top left corner of the rectangle can be inside or outside the widget. If the defined position is outside the screen border, the popup form will be centered in the middle of the screen. This can occur if the PopupRect is too large to fit on the screen, or if it is positioned on or outside the screen border. This ensures that if the application runs on a smaller screen than it is designed for, the popup form will always be visible. The PopupRect property affects all popup forms anchored to a field. You can first instantiate a popup form without the PopupRect property and then set the property to instantiate another popup. If both popup instances remain open, the anchor point of the first popup changes when the size or position of the anchor field changes. This triggers Uniface to reevaluate the position of all popup instances and use the current value of the PopupRect property for all instances, even when the different popups were instantiated with a different value. Example: Setting in ProcScript The following ProcScript sets the PopupRect property for field WID, and displays a form in a drop-down window. ;Detail trigger of WID field newinstance \"POPUPFRM\", \"Popup\", \"windowtype=popup\" $fieldproperties(FLD1) = \"popuprect=5,1,100px,10px\" activate \"Popup\" Copy Figure 1. Popup Window for Popup Rectangle in Field Applies To All widgets except the Grid widget. ucheckbox (CheckBox) colorbox ucolorlist (ColorList) ucombobox (Combo Box) CommandButton DropTarget udropdownlist (DropDownList) ucontainer (FormContainer) EditBox Hyperlink uhtml (HTML Widget) ulistbox (ListBox ) umap (Map) umeter (Meter) (umonthcalendar) MonthCalendar uOcxContainer (OcxContainer) uOleContainer (OleContainer) uoutputbox (OutputBox) Image Name uradiogroup (RadioGroup) urtfeditbox (RichEditBox) uslider (Slider) uspinbutton (SpinButton) utab (Tab) utabex (TabEx) utree (Tree) Related Links Popup Window A popup window displays a form in a secondary window that is anchored to a field. The position of the popup window is configurable, so that it can be displayed outside or inside the boundaries of its parent field. Position Form instance property that defines the position of a popup form relative to its anchor object, which can be a field, popup rectangle, or mouse cursor. The value specifies an edge or corner from which the window starts, and the direction in which it is displayed. This property can be set in ProcScript using newinstance and $windowproperties. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}